description: One of the Sentinel of Liberty's greatest conflicts with his hated arch-nemesis is finally collected! Join Cap & Co. - including Nomad, the Black Crow, the Avengers and more - as Marvel's First Avenger must contend with the diabolical daughter of the Red Skull, survive the Secret Wars and overcome an untimely encounter with old age - all before one stupendous showdown with Herr Skull that will leave you gaping in star-spangled wonder! Collecting CAPTAIN AMERICA (1968) #290-301.
name: TPB

volume.name: Captain America: Death of the Red Skull

description: What would happen if a collection of Deadpool's frozen, severed body parts were to be thrown into a dumpster and then, once thawed, fuse together to form a new - and totally evil - Deadpool? Well, we could tell you - but it'd be way cooler if you read it for yourself! Collecting DEADPOOL (2008) #45-49 and #49.1.
name: Volume 10

description: With a growing sense of uncertainty and despair gripping the nation - and the world - the remnants of the Initiative program are sworn in as federal agents charged with keeping the peace. Their ensuing actions, however, threaten to plunge America's young heroes into civil war! Featuring Avengers: the Initiative stars Thor Girl, Ultragirl, Cloud 9, Komodo and Hardball - plus Firestar, Gravity and some very cool surprises -youth in revolt brings the horror of Fear Itself to the doorstep of a generation! Collecting FEAR ITSELF: YOUTH IN REVOLT #1-6.

description: Travis and Shule find themselves walking right into Malateste’s trap and into the biggest fight of their lives. Shule learns about the headless men, and the fate of Nostradamus is revealed. Meanwhile, an enigmatic object is found at the top of Baal’s tower - a glistening black sphere that could unlock the secret of Travis’ double life and give him the power and memories of the sorcerer Jacomo Terence. That is, if he can avoid having his own mind obliterated in the process.
